title: Woman booked in fatal stabbing of boyfriend in Prairieville
text:
PRAIRIEVILLE, La. (AP) - Ascension Parish sheriff's deputies say a 21-year-old Prairieville man died after argument with his girlfriend turn violent.
Lt. Col. Bobby Webre tells The Advocate ( http://bit.ly/1QU5ogG ) Jonqualya Benton is accused of stabbing her boyfriend, Deshad Perry, in the chest just before midnight Friday. He later died at a hospital in Baton Rouge.
Webre says deputies responded to reports of screaming coming from a home in Prairieville and found the door open when they arrived and a large amount of blood throughout the home.
Webre says a Baton Rouge hospital contacted the sheriff's office to tell deputies it was treating a stab victim who had just arrived in critical condition.
Benton was booked with manslaughter. No bond has been set.
Online jail records do not list an attorney for Benton.
Information from: The Advocate, http://theadvocate.com
